WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.600
Okay, welcome back to mental fitness, I think we have our voice portion or microphone portion

00:08.600 --> 00:14.520
solved and we'll be feeding back those videos as we need.

00:14.520 --> 00:22.080
So welcome back to mental fitness, we're here to talk about stress today.

00:22.080 --> 00:26.040
So when I say that word, does it make you like tighten up?

00:26.040 --> 00:28.560
Does it make you feel like stress is a bad thing?

00:28.560 --> 00:32.200
When I talk about stress, do you get motivated?

00:32.200 --> 00:35.280
Do you get inspired?

00:35.280 --> 00:41.040
And what do you think of when I say the word stress?

00:41.040 --> 00:43.920
So for today's exercise, I actually want you to write it down.

00:43.920 --> 00:50.440
I want you to write down what you think of or what your beliefs are about stress.

00:50.440 --> 00:55.280
So it could be any number of those things, write down, be a little bit specific, but

00:55.320 --> 00:58.840
just take a few moments to do that.

00:58.840 --> 01:06.640
Okay, so now that you've written down what you think of when I say the word stress, you

01:06.640 --> 01:13.760
are going to think of how is this serving me?

01:13.760 --> 01:23.760
So how is my above belief serving me in my writing and my goals in writing?

01:23.760 --> 01:29.360
So after you've taken a few minutes to do that, read it back to yourself.

01:29.360 --> 01:36.200
And oftentimes we get this picture of what our beliefs are really doing for our writing

01:36.200 --> 01:38.440
or our lives.

01:38.440 --> 01:40.800
And you may have not known this before.

01:40.800 --> 01:47.640
And maybe some of you might have predicted that this belief is either causing harm or

01:47.640 --> 01:51.780
causing benefit to your writing and your goals.

01:51.780 --> 01:53.100
So it's important to know.

01:53.100 --> 02:00.840
So for example, if you have the belief that stress is tension and bad, it's likely making

02:00.840 --> 02:09.080
your writing tense and bad because writing just like any activity has a certain stress

02:09.080 --> 02:10.500
on it.

02:10.500 --> 02:19.580
And the reality is or the truth is about stress is that we go through so many stresses in

02:19.580 --> 02:22.580
the day and we do great.

02:22.580 --> 02:25.980
When you eat, it's actually a stress on your body.

02:25.980 --> 02:27.840
But how does it feel?

02:27.840 --> 02:32.480
It feels fantastic most of the time, feels healthy, feels nourishing.

02:32.480 --> 02:40.040
And in the end, it is overall necessary and good for you to eat.

02:40.040 --> 02:45.220
But it is technically a stress on your body, because the food goes in and the body has

02:45.220 --> 02:49.280
to solve the problem of digesting it.

02:49.280 --> 02:52.360
And that's pretty much the definition of stress.

02:52.360 --> 02:56.020
So we're going to work backwards in the next point.

02:56.020 --> 02:59.560
And we're going to say, what do you want to see in your writing?

02:59.560 --> 03:04.320
What do you want as a result in your writing in the area of stress?

03:04.320 --> 03:06.100
So write that down.

03:06.100 --> 03:10.860
So this could be, you know, I want to feel prepared.

03:10.860 --> 03:14.640
I want to feel strong.

03:14.640 --> 03:18.900
I want to feel capable.

03:18.900 --> 03:21.940
I want to feel loose.

03:21.960 --> 03:27.160
And here it is, you write that down, just a few things, like three to five things, write

03:27.160 --> 03:29.680
it down.

03:29.680 --> 03:33.600
Then after you've written that down, like I said, we're going to work backwards.

03:33.600 --> 03:39.000
We're going to see what belief would you have to have about stress in order to accomplish

03:39.000 --> 03:42.720
that goal.

03:42.720 --> 03:50.000
So for example, if you want to be loose in the saddle, you want to be relaxed and not

03:50.060 --> 03:55.460
tense, your belief about stress has to be that stress is good for you.

03:55.460 --> 04:01.580
There's a process in it and that you can let go and be relaxed in it.

04:01.580 --> 04:04.940
So as you've written this out, what you've previously believed in, what it was serving

04:04.940 --> 04:13.140
you for, and then what you want out of it really, or the service that you want and what

04:13.140 --> 04:19.380
belief you have to have to get there, all of a sudden we have a mindset change available

04:19.440 --> 04:20.440
to you.

04:20.440 --> 04:24.720
So you have the opportunity now to believe one and get one result or believe the other

04:24.720 --> 04:27.720
and get another result.

04:27.720 --> 04:34.200
And just like anything, we can decide now to be better with stress or to be truthful

04:34.200 --> 04:39.080
with stress because stress is not the killer.

04:39.080 --> 04:46.480
It's not a bad thing and it's not something that we shouldn't or can't go through.

04:46.580 --> 04:52.380
It's just a process of life that produces really good things.

04:52.380 --> 04:57.060
And the reason why we call this mental fitness is because it's just like fitness.

04:57.060 --> 05:04.060
When you work a muscle, you need to push against resistance in order to build muscle and to

05:04.060 --> 05:06.900
increase strength, increase elasticity.

05:06.900 --> 05:13.620
You need to do things, you need to make actions, you need to be in mindset for your body, not

05:13.620 --> 05:17.760
against your body, in order to produce better health and better fitness.

05:17.760 --> 05:20.200
And it's actually the same mentally.

05:20.200 --> 05:24.560
So essentially what we've done here, we've decided where you're at and where you want

05:24.560 --> 05:33.480
to go with this particular avenue of stress in writing, and you can choose to make a decision

05:33.480 --> 05:39.720
to go forward with something more valuable to your goal.

05:39.820 --> 05:46.460
But in order to keep doing that, we need to have small practical practices to optimize

05:46.460 --> 05:54.040
and systematically go about training our muscles in our mind.

05:54.040 --> 05:59.140
So there's a few things that you can do to do that.

05:59.140 --> 06:03.580
And I like to call them micro stresses or purposeful stresses.

06:03.580 --> 06:08.660
So you're going to purposefully put yourself in an uncomfortable or a different position

06:08.680 --> 06:15.480
similar to a stretch or a lifting maneuver mentally in order to produce something better

06:15.480 --> 06:18.240
for your whole life.

06:18.240 --> 06:22.440
So we're going to go through three examples of what you can do.

06:22.440 --> 06:32.640
So number one, to deal with something physical about your body is you can do therapy on your

06:32.640 --> 06:37.000
body in the way of a cold shower.

06:37.000 --> 06:43.900
You can do exercise every day, which we're already is part of our program.

06:43.900 --> 06:48.180
And you can do something for your body that you know that it needs.

06:48.180 --> 06:53.500
So either that's nutrition, therapy on an old injury, those kinds of things.

06:53.500 --> 06:57.820
If you commit to one of those things for your physical body, then you can change your mental

06:57.820 --> 07:01.740
state about the particular stresses.

07:01.740 --> 07:07.560
Most of the time when people don't go to physical therapy for something physical, it's because

07:07.560 --> 07:09.980
they don't want to be uncomfortable with the pain.

07:09.980 --> 07:14.860
But what it really does is it elongates the pain to be longer and bug them for a longer

07:14.860 --> 07:16.180
time in their life.

07:16.180 --> 07:18.280
And we do the same thing mentally.

07:18.280 --> 07:22.340
So go after it, get after it, do something physical for your body for the sake of the

07:22.340 --> 07:23.340
mental.

07:23.340 --> 07:30.340
So that's cold showers, exercise every day, or a therapy for your body.

07:30.340 --> 07:35.100
And that could even be something like stretching if you would if you prefer mentally to separate

07:35.100 --> 07:37.300
stretching from exercise.

07:37.300 --> 07:45.180
So that's that's a really easy, tangible starting point for you to go because it's so it's so

07:45.180 --> 07:49.220
easy to measure on your on your physical person.

07:49.220 --> 07:52.180
Number two, something social.

07:52.180 --> 08:00.500
So for example, if you are talkative, you can choose once a week, you are going to spend

08:00.500 --> 08:09.660
10 minutes listening to somebody very, very actively and intensively to stretch your ability

08:09.660 --> 08:14.620
to deal with your strengths and weaknesses in your mind.

08:14.620 --> 08:20.340
If you're less talkative, maybe you want to stretch your ability by being the one sharing

08:20.340 --> 08:21.420
with another person.

08:21.460 --> 08:26.540
So once a week, you can spend 10 minutes talking to a stranger, talking to your spouse, talking

08:26.540 --> 08:32.780
to someone else, a friend, and interacting in a way that's going to stretch you mentally.

08:32.780 --> 08:37.300
The point is to get out of your comfort zone, okay?

08:37.300 --> 08:42.820
And then number three is to do something personally or individually with your body.

08:42.820 --> 08:48.740
So that can be even the meditation we did two weeks ago before you get on and ride.

08:48.740 --> 08:55.500
It could be something you do in the morning where you wake up and you set yourself up

08:55.500 --> 09:00.100
for the day mentally, a state of mind that you want to put yourself in, those kinds of

09:00.100 --> 09:05.180
things that are personal and individual, and it just involves you.

09:05.180 --> 09:11.740
So those are some very, very broad examples of you putting micro stresses on yourself

09:11.740 --> 09:17.700
to help work the mental muscle of your mind so they can serve you in your life and your

09:17.700 --> 09:21.580
goals even better than it already is.

09:21.580 --> 09:23.180
As always, for the sake of the horse.

